From 5a3d98a46847daae0740df1ba1f318509dada4af Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dev <dev@local>
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 15:40:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix TicketDetails data binding, event wiring, and controller
 duplication
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Data binding (TicketDetails.js)
- Read the real camelCase API fields (ticketID, subject, status, priority,
  raisedBy, authority, requestType, created, closeDate, targetDate) instead of
  PascalCase / non-existent names (StatusID, CreatedDate, SLADate, ...). Pills,
  names and dates were all binding to undefined.
- SLA pill now derives from targetDate (model has no SLA field).
- Layout/internal detection reads requestID; store the correct request type.

Event wiring
- Add FieldHandlers.bind() to Events.bind() — editing tech/category/priority/
  target date did nothing and never marked the ticket dirty.
- Resolve layout once after the fetch, then restore the saved tab, so the
  layout default no longer clobbers a returning user's tab.

Save
- Send the real ticketID. A null ID made SaveTicket take the INSERT path and
  silently create a duplicate ticket.

Storage keys (STORAGE_KEYS.js)
- Add dedicated TD_ACTIVE_TAB / TD_PANES_COLLAPSED; the page was reusing
  ADMIN_SUB_PAGE and TABLE_PAGE_NAME, colliding with other pages.

Backend (TicketController.cs)
- Remove the dead duplicate GetTicketDetail (no JS caller; skipped the id
  validation + NotFound handling that TicketDetailsController.GetTicketDetail has).
---
 Controllers/Tickets/TicketController.cs  |  11 +--
 wwwroot/js/Core/STORAGE_KEYS.js          |   5 ++
 wwwroot/js/Pages/Ticket/TicketDetails.js | 105 ++++++++++++-----------
 3 files changed, 65 insertions(+), 56 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Controllers/Tickets/TicketController.cs b/Controllers/Tickets/TicketController.cs
index c2e19b9..499c5d5 100644
